{"id":435,"date":"2020-02-29T21:04:53","date_gmt":"2020-02-29T21:04:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/travellovelanguage\/"},"modified":"2023-03-04T07:50:47","modified_gmt":"2023-03-04T07:50:47","slug":"travellovelanguage","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/travellovelanguage\/","title":{"rendered":"What&#8217;s Your Travel Love Language? | 5 Languages of Love: Travel Version"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>What is your travel love language? <\/strong><\/h1>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">According to the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.5lovelanguages.com\/languages\/words-of-affirmation\/\">Love Language book<\/a>, it is said that we all have different love languages that determine how we most receive love. It helps to know your own, your partner\u2019s, family\/friends love language so that you can express love in the way that most resonates with them. Let\u2019s put a travel spin on the \u2018love languages\u2019. Which one are you?<\/p>\n<h1 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>\u2063<br \/>\nWords of Affirmation <\/strong><\/h1>\n<div class=\"\n          image-block-outer-wrapper\n          layout-caption-below\n          design-layout-inline\n          combination-animation-none\n          individual-animation-none\n          individual-text-animation-none\n        \" data-test=\"image-block-inline-outer-wrapper\"><\/p>\n<figure class=\"\n              sqs-block-image-figure\n              intrinsic\n            \" style=\"max-width: 1242px;\"><\/p>\n<div class=\"image-block-wrapper\" data-animation-role=\"image\">\n<div class=\"sqs-image-shape-container-element\n\n              has-aspect-ratio\n            \"><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"thumb-image\" src=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583009680029-4T5XP9TP3NOB26YD6EAR\/travellovelanguage\" alt=\"A sweet message from my best-friend that made me cry after our trip to San Diego.\" data-image=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583009680029-4T5XP9TP3NOB26YD6EAR\/travellovelanguage\" data-image-dimensions=\"1242x639\" data-image-focal-point=\"0.5,0.5\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"5e5acf8daf79a531e0b89aa4\" data-type=\"image\"><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><figcaption class=\"image-caption-wrapper\">\n<div class=\"image-caption\">\n<p class=\"\">A sweet message from my best-friend that made me cry after our trip to San Diego.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">After the trip together, you receive a text that says \u201comg you are the best travel partner EVER!!! Let\u2019s do it again ASAP\u201d or they thank you endlessly for embarking on a journey with them. This is music to your ears and boom, you\u2019ve already booked another trip together. \u2063<\/p>\n<h1 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong><br \/>\nPhysical Touch<\/strong><\/h1>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/47k6NR9rgh4?wmode=opaque&amp;enablejsapi=1\" width=\"854\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><br \/>\n<\/iframe><\/p>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">You will freak if you can\u2019t sit together on the plane bc then who will you hold hands with??? Y\u2019all are all boo\u2019d up in the Airbnb giving each other massages and doing Lord knows what else. The entire city is sick of your PDA but you\u2019re quite literally so wrapped up in each other that you hardly notice. \u2063<\/p>\n<h1 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">\u2063<br \/>\n<strong>Quality Time<\/strong><\/h1>\n<div class=\"\n          image-block-outer-wrapper\n          layout-caption-below\n          design-layout-inline\n          combination-animation-none\n          individual-animation-none\n          individual-text-animation-none\n        \" data-test=\"image-block-inline-outer-wrapper\"><\/p>\n<figure class=\"\n              sqs-block-image-figure\n              intrinsic\n            \" style=\"max-width: 1242px;\"><\/p>\n<div class=\"image-block-wrapper\" data-animation-role=\"image\">\n<div class=\"sqs-image-shape-container-element\n\n              has-aspect-ratio\n            \"><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"thumb-image\" src=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583008815012-E9IJG9QB9G8SXUSKOC03\/travellovelanguages\" alt=\"travellovelanguages\" data-image=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583008815012-E9IJG9QB9G8SXUSKOC03\/travellovelanguages\" data-image-dimensions=\"1242x1239\" data-image-focal-point=\"0.5,0.5\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"5e5acc266b59fb4daced36e6\" data-type=\"image\"><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">You\u2019re road-tripping to a campsite with no cell service so you can focus completely on each other. You\u2019ll be roasting stores and playing card games. Honestly, you could be sleeping in a ditch but it doesn\u2019t matter as long as you\u2019re together. \u2063<\/p>\n<h1 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">\u2063<br \/>\n<strong>Acts of Service<\/strong><\/h1>\n<div class=\"\n          image-block-outer-wrapper\n          layout-caption-below\n          design-layout-inline\n          combination-animation-none\n          individual-animation-none\n          individual-text-animation-none\n        \" data-test=\"image-block-inline-outer-wrapper\"><\/p>\n<figure class=\"\n              sqs-block-image-figure\n              intrinsic\n            \" style=\"max-width: 1500px;\"><\/p>\n<div class=\"image-block-wrapper\" data-animation-role=\"image\">\n<div class=\"sqs-image-shape-container-element\n\n              has-aspect-ratio\n            \"><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"thumb-image\" src=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583009270469-OAXC7TJLNZN6117JS0EH\/travellovelanguage\" alt=\"travellovelanguage\" data-image=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583009270469-OAXC7TJLNZN6117JS0EH\/travellovelanguage\" data-image-dimensions=\"1500x1991\" data-image-focal-point=\"0.5,0.5\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"5e5acdf4e0cc0e63b16c0b1c\" data-type=\"image\"><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">They booked the entire trip for you, from start to finish. They even helped you pack your bags. They make you breakfast in the B&amp;B every morning and make dinner restaurants at that Michelin star restaurant you\u2019ve been dying to visit. They\u2019re taking the most IG worthy photos of you, getting all your angles. It\u2019s your world baby, and everyone else is just living in it. \u2063<\/p>\n<h1 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">\u2063<br \/>\n<strong>Receiving Gifts<\/strong><\/h1>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">OMG they surprised you with a fully paid trip to a place you\u2019ve had on your lock screen for ages. You\u2019re all set and they find you the perfect souvenir to remember your baecation by once the trip ends. \u2063<\/p>\n<div class=\"\n          image-block-outer-wrapper\n          layout-caption-below\n          design-layout-inline\n          combination-animation-none\n          individual-animation-none\n          individual-text-animation-none\n        \" data-test=\"image-block-inline-outer-wrapper\"><\/p>\n<figure class=\"\n              sqs-block-image-figure\n              intrinsic\n            \" style=\"max-width: 1080px;\"><\/p>\n<div class=\"image-block-wrapper\" data-animation-role=\"image\">\n<div class=\"sqs-image-shape-container-element\n\n              has-aspect-ratio\n            \"><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"thumb-image\" src=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583006874223-ND3C5VGQ940JEMJQN1GQ\/travellovelanguages\" alt=\"travellovelanguages\" data-image=\"https:\/\/images.squarespace-cdn.com\/content\/v1\/57a43cf715d5db0bee1397d9\/1583006874223-ND3C5VGQ940JEMJQN1GQ\/travellovelanguages\" data-image-dimensions=\"1080x1080\" data-image-focal-point=\"0.5,0.5\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"5e5ac498e6c06e061f8d9b1a\" data-type=\"image\"><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<h2 style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; text-align: left;\"><strong>\u2063<br \/>\nCan you identify with one of these love languages? <\/strong><\/h2>\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\" data-rte-preserve-empty=\"true\">\n<p class=\"\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Or maybe travel is your love language in general! I personally feel that mine is words of affirmation and physical touch, based on previous trips. Might be quality time too lmao! <a href=\"https:\/\/www.5lovelanguages.com\/languages\/words-of-affirmation\/\">You can click here<\/a> to access the actual quiz because travel aside &#8211; understanding each other love languages can really help us love each other more effectively and actually feel loved. <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/2PBOqfc\">You can purchase the actual book here.<\/a><\/p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>You Might Also Enjoy:<\/strong><\/h1>\n<div class=\"\n  summary-block-wrapper\n\n  summary-block-collection-type-blog\n\n  summary-block-setting-text-size-small\n  summary-block-setting-text-align-center\n\n  summary-block-setting-design-carousel\n  summary-block-setting-design-list-thumbnail-left\n\n  summary-block-setting-metadata-position-below-content\n  summary-block-setting-primary-metadata-none\n  summary-block-setting-secondary-metadata-none\n\n  summary-block-setting-show-thumbnail\n  summary-block-setting-show-title\n  summary-block-setting-show-price\n  summary-block-setting-hide-excerpt\n  summary-block-setting-show-read-more-link\n\n  sqs-galle